<title>BELGIUM: Belgian Quick sizzles in early trade.</title>
<headline>Belgian Quick sizzles in early trade.</headline>
<dateline>BRUSSELS 1997-05-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in Belgian hamburger chain Quick sizzled in early Brussels bourse trade on Wednesday, adding to spectacular gains made since the beginning of the week on a broker upgrade.</p>
<p>Quick was up 110 francs, or 5.87 percent, at 1,985 francs after only 15 minutes of bourse trade while most other issues were lower. Shares in Quick's controlling shareholder, blue chip retailer GIB were five francs lower at 1,575 francs.</p>
<p>Quick's share has now risen more than 10 percent since Monday, when brokerage BBL/Vermeulen-Raemdonck said it had raised the company to &quot;hold&quot; from &quot;sell&quot;.</p>
